[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1117},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fjs-weird-world-56-object-create-prototypal-inheritance\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fjs-weird-world-56-object-create-prototypal-inheritance\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fjs-weird-world-56-object-create-prototypal-inheritance\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fjs-weird-world-56-object-create-prototypal-inheritance\u002F":1092,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F24\u002Fjs-weird-world-56-object-create-prototypal-inheritance\u002F":1101},"\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F20190524\u002F4206229622\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1075,"date":1076,"description":1077,"extension":1078,"lang":1079,"meta":1080,"navigation":223,"path":1081,"readingMinutes":1082,"seo":1083,"standalone":1084,"stem":1085,"tags":1086,"tldr":1089,"updated":1076,"url":1090,"__hash__":1091},"content\u002Fen\u002FJsWeirdWorld\u002Fjs-weird-world-56-object-create-prototypal-inheritance.md","[JS Weird World] No.56 Object.create and Pure Prototypal Inheritance","1000403872",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1067},"minimark",[11,16,29,32,39,42,45,143,150,157,260,263,270,273,279,282,288,291,432,438,441,454,460,463,593,599,602,742,748,763,769,774,787,793,803,809,817,820,826,829,835,972,1002,1008,1022,1039,1043,1052,1056,1063],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24,25,28],"p",{},"By now we've already seen how to build objects with function constructors, and we've looked at why they showed up in the first place — they exist to mimic other languages that can't really do prototypal inheritance. So this is where things get a little awkward. In those other languages you use ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"class"," to define what an object should do, and then ",[21,26,27],{},"new"," to create one. That's exactly the thing function constructors are trying to imitate.",[17,30,31],{},"And honestly, some people lean way more into prototypal inheritance than classical inheritance when they're writing code.",[17,33,34,35,38],{},"There's also one more way to create objects in JavaScript, and modern browsers have it built in: ",[21,36,37],{},"Object.create",". So let's go through an example and think about prototypal inheritance while we're at it.",[12,40,37],{"id":41},"objectcreate",[17,43,44],{},"First, let's build a new object using object literal syntax:",[46,47,52],"pre",{"className":48,"code":49,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","var person = {\n  firstname: 'Default',\n  lastname: 'Default',\n  greet: function() {\n    return 'Hi' + this.firstname;\n  }\n}\n","js","",[21,53,54,73,86,96,112,131,137],{"__ignoreMap":51},[55,56,59,63,67,70],"span",{"class":57,"line":58},"line",1,[55,60,62],{"class":61},"sWyjQ","var",[55,64,66],{"class":65},"sMAXC"," person ",[55,68,69],{"class":61},"=",[55,71,72],{"class":65}," {\n",[55,74,76,79,83],{"class":57,"line":75},2,[55,77,78],{"class":65},"  firstname: ",[55,80,82],{"class":81},"sTRMh","'Default'",[55,84,85],{"class":65},",\n",[55,87,89,92,94],{"class":57,"line":88},3,[55,90,91],{"class":65},"  lastname: ",[55,93,82],{"class":81},[55,95,85],{"class":65},[55,97,99,103,106,109],{"class":57,"line":98},4,[55,100,102],{"class":101},"sj_SG","  greet",[55,104,105],{"class":65},": ",[55,107,108],{"class":61},"function",[55,110,111],{"class":65},"() {\n",[55,113,115,118,121,124,128],{"class":57,"line":114},5,[55,116,117],{"class":61},"    return",[55,119,120],{"class":81}," 'Hi'",[55,122,123],{"class":61}," +",[55,125,127],{"class":126},"sCcAr"," this",[55,129,130],{"class":65},".firstname;\n",[55,132,134],{"class":57,"line":133},6,[55,135,136],{"class":65},"  }\n",[55,138,140],{"class":57,"line":139},7,[55,141,142],{"class":65},"}\n",[17,144,145,146,149],{},"One thing to keep in mind here: an object doesn't create a new execution context. So when you don't write ",[21,147,148],{},"this",", it'll go straight to the global environment to look things up.",[17,151,152,153,156],{},"Another thing to note — everything coming up is doing the same thing ",[55,154,155],{}," creating an object",", just using a method that modern browsers ship with:",[46,158,160],{"className":48,"code":159,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"var person = {\n  firstname: 'Default',\n  lastname: 'Default',\n  greet: function() {\n    return 'Hi' + this.firstname;\n  }\n}\n\nvar john = Object.create(person); \u002F\u002F pass in person\nconsole.log(john);\n",[21,161,162,172,180,188,198,210,214,218,225,248],{"__ignoreMap":51},[55,163,164,166,168,170],{"class":57,"line":58},[55,165,62],{"class":61},[55,167,66],{"class":65},[55,169,69],{"class":61},[55,171,72],{"class":65},[55,173,174,176,178],{"class":57,"line":75},[55,175,78],{"class":65},[55,177,82],{"class":81},[55,179,85],{"class":65},[55,181,182,184,186],{"class":57,"line":88},[55,183,91],{"class":65},[55,185,82],{"class":81},[55,187,85],{"class":65},[55,189,190,192,194,196],{"class":57,"line":98},[55,191,102],{"class":101},[55,193,105],{"class":65},[55,195,108],{"class":61},[55,197,111],{"class":65},[55,199,200,202,204,206,208],{"class":57,"line":114},[55,201,117],{"class":61},[55,203,120],{"class":81},[55,205,123],{"class":61},[55,207,127],{"class":126},[55,209,130],{"class":65},[55,211,212],{"class":57,"line":133},[55,213,136],{"class":65},[55,215,216],{"class":57,"line":139},[55,217,142],{"class":65},[55,219,221],{"class":57,"line":220},8,[55,222,224],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":223},true,"\n",[55,226,228,230,233,235,238,241,244],{"class":57,"line":227},9,[55,229,62],{"class":61},[55,231,232],{"class":65}," john ",[55,234,69],{"class":61},[55,236,237],{"class":65}," Object.",[55,239,240],{"class":101},"create",[55,242,243],{"class":65},"(person); ",[55,245,247],{"class":246},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F pass in person\n",[55,249,251,254,257],{"class":57,"line":250},10,[55,252,253],{"class":65},"console.",[55,255,256],{"class":101},"log",[55,258,259],{"class":65},"(john);\n",[17,261,262],{},"And here's where something weird happens:",[17,264,265],{},[266,267],"img",{"alt":268,"src":269},"Console showing an empty object","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FUuchFaz.png",[17,271,272],{},"For a second I thought it was a browser display issue, because the example in the course looked like this:",[17,274,275],{},[266,276],{"alt":277,"src":278},"Course example output","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLfmVlEm.png",[17,280,281],{},"So I tried it in a Chrome build to compare:",[17,283,284],{},[266,285],{"alt":286,"src":287},"Chrome version output","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FIFNkUXB.png",[17,289,290],{},"Same result. So I tried another way to pull things out of the object:",[46,292,294],{"className":48,"code":293,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"var person = {\n  firstname: 'Default',\n  lastname: 'Default',\n  greet: function() {\n    return 'Hi' + this.firstname;\n  }\n}\n\nvar john = Object.create(person); \u002F\u002F pass in person\nconsole.log(john);\nconsole.log('----');\nconsole.log(john.firstname);\nconsole.log(john.lastname);\nconsole.log(john.greet());\n",[21,295,296,306,314,322,332,344,348,352,356,372,380,396,406,416],{"__ignoreMap":51},[55,297,298,300,302,304],{"class":57,"line":58},[55,299,62],{"class":61},[55,301,66],{"class":65},[55,303,69],{"class":61},[55,305,72],{"class":65},[55,307,308,310,312],{"class":57,"line":75},[55,309,78],{"class":65},[55,311,82],{"class":81},[55,313,85],{"class":65},[55,315,316,318,320],{"class":57,"line":88},[55,317,91],{"class":65},[55,319,82],{"class":81},[55,321,85],{"class":65},[55,323,324,326,328,330],{"class":57,"line":98},[55,325,102],{"class":101},[55,327,105],{"class":65},[55,329,108],{"class":61},[55,331,111],{"class":65},[55,333,334,336,338,340,342],{"class":57,"line":114},[55,335,117],{"class":61},[55,337,120],{"class":81},[55,339,123],{"class":61},[55,341,127],{"class":126},[55,343,130],{"class":65},[55,345,346],{"class":57,"line":133},[55,347,136],{"class":65},[55,349,350],{"class":57,"line":139},[55,351,142],{"class":65},[55,353,354],{"class":57,"line":220},[55,355,224],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":223},[55,357,358,360,362,364,366,368,370],{"class":57,"line":227},[55,359,62],{"class":61},[55,361,232],{"class":65},[55,363,69],{"class":61},[55,365,237],{"class":65},[55,367,240],{"class":101},[55,369,243],{"class":65},[55,371,247],{"class":246},[55,373,374,376,378],{"class":57,"line":250},[55,375,253],{"class":65},[55,377,256],{"class":101},[55,379,259],{"class":65},[55,381,383,385,387,390,393],{"class":57,"line":382},11,[55,384,253],{"class":65},[55,386,256],{"class":101},[55,388,389],{"class":65},"(",[55,391,392],{"class":81},"'----'",[55,394,395],{"class":65},");\n",[55,397,399,401,403],{"class":57,"line":398},12,[55,400,253],{"class":65},[55,402,256],{"class":101},[55,404,405],{"class":65},"(john.firstname);\n",[55,407,409,411,413],{"class":57,"line":408},13,[55,410,253],{"class":65},[55,412,256],{"class":101},[55,414,415],{"class":65},"(john.lastname);\n",[55,417,419,421,423,426,429],{"class":57,"line":418},14,[55,420,253],{"class":65},[55,422,256],{"class":101},[55,424,425],{"class":65},"(john.",[55,427,428],{"class":101},"greet",[55,430,431],{"class":65},"());\n",[17,433,434],{},[266,435],{"alt":436,"src":437},"Accessing properties through the prototype","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FX8ETPTk.png",[17,439,440],{},"So you can actually grab the stuff inside the object — but why does it show up as an empty object? PJCHENder's article explains it:",[442,443,444],"blockquote",{},[17,445,446,447,450,451,453],{},"With ",[21,448,449],{},"Object.create()"," you create an empty object, and whatever you pass into ",[21,452,449],{}," becomes that object's prototype.",[17,455,456,457,459],{},"So the reason is this: calling ",[21,458,449],{}," creates an empty object, and then turns the argument you passed in into that object's prototype.",[17,461,462],{},"And with this approach we can flexibly override or tweak properties and methods:",[46,464,466],{"className":48,"code":465,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"var person = {\n  firstname: 'Default',\n  lastname: 'Default',\n  greet: function() {\n    return 'Hi' + this.firstname;\n  }\n}\n\nvar john = Object.create(person); \u002F\u002F pass in person\nconsole.log(john);\nconsole.log(john.firstname);\njohn.firstname = 'John';\nconsole.log('----');\nconsole.log(john.firstname);\n",[21,467,468,478,486,494,504,516,520,524,528,544,552,560,573,585],{"__ignoreMap":51},[55,469,470,472,474,476],{"class":57,"line":58},[55,471,62],{"class":61},[55,473,66],{"class":65},[55,475,69],{"class":61},[55,477,72],{"class":65},[55,479,480,482,484],{"class":57,"line":75},[55,481,78],{"class":65},[55,483,82],{"class":81},[55,485,85],{"class":65},[55,487,488,490,492],{"class":57,"line":88},[55,489,91],{"class":65},[55,491,82],{"class":81},[55,493,85],{"class":65},[55,495,496,498,500,502],{"class":57,"line":98},[55,497,102],{"class":101},[55,499,105],{"class":65},[55,501,108],{"class":61},[55,503,111],{"class":65},[55,505,506,508,510,512,514],{"class":57,"line":114},[55,507,117],{"class":61},[55,509,120],{"class":81},[55,511,123],{"class":61},[55,513,127],{"class":126},[55,515,130],{"class":65},[55,517,518],{"class":57,"line":133},[55,519,136],{"class":65},[55,521,522],{"class":57,"line":139},[55,523,142],{"class":65},[55,525,526],{"class":57,"line":220},[55,527,224],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":223},[55,529,530,532,534,536,538,540,542],{"class":57,"line":227},[55,531,62],{"class":61},[55,533,232],{"class":65},[55,535,69],{"class":61},[55,537,237],{"class":65},[55,539,240],{"class":101},[55,541,243],{"class":65},[55,543,247],{"class":246},[55,545,546,548,550],{"class":57,"line":250},[55,547,253],{"class":65},[55,549,256],{"class":101},[55,551,259],{"class":65},[55,553,554,556,558],{"class":57,"line":382},[55,555,253],{"class":65},[55,557,256],{"class":101},[55,559,405],{"class":65},[55,561,562,565,567,570],{"class":57,"line":398},[55,563,564],{"class":65},"john.firstname ",[55,566,69],{"class":61},[55,568,569],{"class":81}," 'John'",[55,571,572],{"class":65},";\n",[55,574,575,577,579,581,583],{"class":57,"line":408},[55,576,253],{"class":65},[55,578,256],{"class":101},[55,580,389],{"class":65},[55,582,392],{"class":81},[55,584,395],{"class":65},[55,586,587,589,591],{"class":57,"line":418},[55,588,253],{"class":65},[55,590,256],{"class":101},[55,592,405],{"class":65},[17,594,595],{},[266,596],{"alt":597,"src":598},"Overriding firstname on the object","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FHrvh7LG.png",[17,600,601],{},"The nice part is that we keep the prototype around and can still use it:",[46,603,605],{"className":48,"code":604,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"var person = {\n  firstname: 'Default',\n  lastname: 'Default',\n  greet: function() {\n    return 'Hi' + this.firstname;\n  }\n}\n\nvar john = Object.create(person); \u002F\u002F pass in person\nconsole.log(john);\nconsole.log(john.firstname);\njohn.firstname = 'John';\nconsole.log('----');\nconsole.log(john.firstname);\nconsole.log(john.greet());\n",[21,606,607,617,625,633,643,655,659,663,667,683,691,699,709,721,729],{"__ignoreMap":51},[55,608,609,611,613,615],{"class":57,"line":58},[55,610,62],{"class":61},[55,612,66],{"class":65},[55,614,69],{"class":61},[55,616,72],{"class":65},[55,618,619,621,623],{"class":57,"line":75},[55,620,78],{"class":65},[55,622,82],{"class":81},[55,624,85],{"class":65},[55,626,627,629,631],{"class":57,"line":88},[55,628,91],{"class":65},[55,630,82],{"class":81},[55,632,85],{"class":65},[55,634,635,637,639,641],{"class":57,"line":98},[55,636,102],{"class":101},[55,638,105],{"class":65},[55,640,108],{"class":61},[55,642,111],{"class":65},[55,644,645,647,649,651,653],{"class":57,"line":114},[55,646,117],{"class":61},[55,648,120],{"class":81},[55,650,123],{"class":61},[55,652,127],{"class":126},[55,654,130],{"class":65},[55,656,657],{"class":57,"line":133},[55,658,136],{"class":65},[55,660,661],{"class":57,"line":139},[55,662,142],{"class":65},[55,664,665],{"class":57,"line":220},[55,666,224],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":223},[55,668,669,671,673,675,677,679,681],{"class":57,"line":227},[55,670,62],{"class":61},[55,672,232],{"class":65},[55,674,69],{"class":61},[55,676,237],{"class":65},[55,678,240],{"class":101},[55,680,243],{"class":65},[55,682,247],{"class":246},[55,684,685,687,689],{"class":57,"line":250},[55,686,253],{"class":65},[55,688,256],{"class":101},[55,690,259],{"class":65},[55,692,693,695,697],{"class":57,"line":382},[55,694,253],{"class":65},[55,696,256],{"class":101},[55,698,405],{"class":65},[55,700,701,703,705,707],{"class":57,"line":398},[55,702,564],{"class":65},[55,704,69],{"class":61},[55,706,569],{"class":81},[55,708,572],{"class":65},[55,710,711,713,715,717,719],{"class":57,"line":408},[55,712,253],{"class":65},[55,714,256],{"class":101},[55,716,389],{"class":65},[55,718,392],{"class":81},[55,720,395],{"class":65},[55,722,723,725,727],{"class":57,"line":418},[55,724,253],{"class":65},[55,726,256],{"class":101},[55,728,405],{"class":65},[55,730,732,734,736,738,740],{"class":57,"line":731},15,[55,733,253],{"class":65},[55,735,256],{"class":101},[55,737,425],{"class":65},[55,739,428],{"class":101},[55,741,431],{"class":65},[17,743,744],{},[266,745],{"alt":746,"src":747},"Prototype still holds Default while object has John","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FdF1zGrO.png",[17,749,750,751,754,755,758,759,762],{},"Even though ",[21,752,753],{},"john"," now has its own ",[21,756,757],{},"firstname",", the prototype still holds ",[21,760,761],{},"Default",".",[17,764,765],{},[266,766],{"alt":767,"src":768},"Prototype chain showing Default preserved","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FMNX7Rxu.png",[442,770,771],{},[17,772,773],{},"And this is exactly what this chapter means by pure prototypal inheritance.",[17,775,776,777,779,780,783,784,786],{},"So with ",[21,778,449],{}," we can override and shadow properties and methods. All we have to do is add properties and methods to ",[21,781,782],{},"person",", and then use ",[21,785,449],{}," so the new object inherits them too. That's pure prototypal inheritance.",[12,788,790,791],{"id":789},"when-a-project-is-too-old-to-support-objectcreate","When a project is too old to support ",[21,792,449],{},[17,794,795,796,798,799,802],{},"But here's something to watch out for: ",[21,797,449],{}," is only supported in newer browsers. So if your project needs to run on older browsers or environments, you can't use this approach — you'll need a ",[21,800,801],{},"polyfill"," instead.",[17,804,805],{},[266,806],{"alt":807,"src":808},"polyfill diagram","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVOMeRnw.png",[442,810,811],{},[17,812,813,814,816],{},"A ",[21,815,801],{}," adds functionality that's missing from the JavaScript engine, baking the feature into your program. So no matter what code you're working with, you can use this technique to check whether the engine has a feature and add it if it doesn't.",[17,818,819],{},"The course's explanation here is pretty vague, so let me lean on some other references.",[17,821,822],{},[266,823],{"alt":824,"src":825},"Image source: PJCHENder","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQIj1dSo.png",[17,827,828],{},"After checking PJCHENder's explanation it got a lot clearer, so let's understand it through an example.",[17,830,831,832,834],{},"The situation today is that the browser is too old and doesn't support ",[21,833,449],{},". Here's what you can do:",[46,836,838],{"className":48,"code":837,"language":50,"meta":51,"style":51},"if (!Object.create()) {\n  Object.create = function (o) {\n    if (arguments.length > 1) {\n      throw new Error('Object.create implementation only accepts the first parameter.');\n    }\n    function F() {}\n    F.prototype = o;\n    return new F();\n  }\n}\n",[21,839,840,859,881,904,922,927,938,953,964,968],{"__ignoreMap":51},[55,841,842,845,848,851,854,856],{"class":57,"line":58},[55,843,844],{"class":61},"if",[55,846,847],{"class":65}," (",[55,849,850],{"class":61},"!",[55,852,853],{"class":65},"Object.",[55,855,240],{"class":101},[55,857,858],{"class":65},"()) {\n",[55,860,861,864,866,869,872,874,878],{"class":57,"line":75},[55,862,863],{"class":65},"  Object.",[55,865,240],{"class":101},[55,867,868],{"class":61}," =",[55,870,871],{"class":61}," function",[55,873,847],{"class":65},[55,875,877],{"class":876},"s_sBn","o",[55,879,880],{"class":65},") {\n",[55,882,883,886,888,891,893,896,899,902],{"class":57,"line":88},[55,884,885],{"class":61},"    if",[55,887,847],{"class":65},[55,889,890],{"class":126},"arguments",[55,892,762],{"class":65},[55,894,895],{"class":126},"length",[55,897,898],{"class":61}," >",[55,900,901],{"class":126}," 1",[55,903,880],{"class":65},[55,905,906,909,912,915,917,920],{"class":57,"line":98},[55,907,908],{"class":61},"      throw",[55,910,911],{"class":61}," new",[55,913,914],{"class":101}," Error",[55,916,389],{"class":65},[55,918,919],{"class":81},"'Object.create implementation only accepts the first parameter.'",[55,921,395],{"class":65},[55,923,924],{"class":57,"line":114},[55,925,926],{"class":65},"    }\n",[55,928,929,932,935],{"class":57,"line":133},[55,930,931],{"class":61},"    function",[55,933,934],{"class":101}," F",[55,936,937],{"class":65},"() {}\n",[55,939,940,943,945,948,950],{"class":57,"line":139},[55,941,942],{"class":126},"    F",[55,944,762],{"class":65},[55,946,947],{"class":126},"prototype",[55,949,868],{"class":61},[55,951,952],{"class":65}," o;\n",[55,954,955,957,959,961],{"class":57,"line":220},[55,956,117],{"class":61},[55,958,911],{"class":61},[55,960,934],{"class":101},[55,962,963],{"class":65},"();\n",[55,965,966],{"class":57,"line":227},[55,967,136],{"class":65},[55,969,970],{"class":57,"line":250},[55,971,142],{"class":65},[17,973,974,975,978,979,981,982,985,986,988,989,991,992,994,995,998,999,1001],{},"Let me walk through the code. First, we use ",[21,976,977],{},"if (!Object.create())"," to check whether the browser supports ",[21,980,449],{},". If it doesn't, that returns ",[21,983,984],{},"undefined",", and the ",[21,987,850],{}," in front flips the result, converting ",[21,990,984],{}," into a boolean. The boolean value of ",[21,993,984],{}," is ",[21,996,997],{},"false",", so what this line really says is: when ",[21,1000,449],{}," doesn't exist, run the code inside.",[17,1003,1004],{},[266,1005],{"alt":1006,"src":1007},"The boolean value of undefined is false","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F7v3w5NB.png",[17,1009,1010,1011,1014,1015,1018,1019,1021],{},"Next, ",[21,1012,1013],{},"if (arguments.length > 1)"," means that if more than one argument gets passed in, it throws the error message \"",[21,1016,1017],{},"Object.create implementation only accepts the first parameter.","\" — basically, ",[21,1020,449],{}," only accepts one argument.",[17,1023,1024,1025,1028,1029,1032,1033,1036,1037,762],{},"The last bit is ",[21,1026,1027],{},"function F() {}",", which creates an empty object, then puts the argument you passed in into ",[21,1030,1031],{},"F.prototype",", and finally returns it the function-constructor way with ",[21,1034,1035],{},"return new F();",". That gets you the same effect as the original ",[21,1038,449],{},[12,1040,1042],{"id":1041},"image-source","Image source",[17,1044,1045],{},[1046,1047,1051],"a",{"href":1048,"rel":1049},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.udemy.com\u002Fjavascriptjs\u002F",[1050],"nofollow","JavaScript 全攻略:克服 JS 奇怪的部分",[12,1053,1055],{"id":1054},"references","References",[17,1057,1058],{},[1046,1059,1062],{"href":1060,"rel":1061},"https:\u002F\u002Fpjchender.blogspot.com\u002F2016\u002F06\u002Fjavascriptprototypal-inheritance.html",[1050],"PJCHENder",[1064,1065,1066],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.s